title: imgonnagetyouback

description.plain:
In “imgonnagetyouback,” Taylor Swift describes a story about not knowing whether she wants an ex-lover back or revenge for what he did to her. It was the first surprise track released on the second side of THE TORTURED POETS DEPARTMENT.

The song’s title stylization is seemingly a reference to The 1975’s 2013 song, “Fallingforyou,” which was sung to her by Matty Healy, Taylor’s rumored ex-boyfriend and subject of several TTPD songs, in 2014.

Along with another touch in how the lyrics,

Bygones will be bygone, eras fadin' into grey (Fading into grey)

Talks about her latest “era”, Midnights, fading into a shade of grey. Which we know as the original version Of THE TORTURED POETS DEPARTMENT, but with Swift’s easter egg challenges growing with level fan speculate it wouldn’t just be hidden within the lyrics, but in everything there’s always an exception. So the lyrics:

Even if it’s handcuffed, I’m leavin' here with you

Have a direct hint to the seventh track “Fresh Out The Slammer”, presenting her relationship as in being a prison.
